  "prompt": "How can one word become three words after repeating three times like Trump's \"three words: jobs, jobs, jobs\"?",
  "response": "When a word is repeated three times, it remains the same word, not three distinct words. In Trump's case, \"jobs\" is one word repeated three times for emphasis. This rhetorical device is called repetition, which is used to:\n\n1. Stress the importance of a concept\n2. Create a memorable phrase\n3. Draw attention to a specific idea\n\nSo \"jobs, jobs, jobs\" is technically still just one word repeated three times, not three separate words.",
